WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.800
AI is not waiting only for smarter code. It is waiting for a bigger power plug.

00:00:05.800 --> 00:00:10.600
The Kardashev scale is a civilization's power meter.

00:00:10.600 --> 00:00:15.200
Today humanity sits around Type 0.73.

00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:20.200
Type I sounds close, until you remember the scale is logarithmic.

00:00:20.200 --> 00:00:25.900
That tiny jump means roughly 500 to 600 times more usable power.

00:00:25.900 --> 00:00:30.900
So AI stops being only a model story. It becomes a grid story.

00:00:30.900 --> 00:00:36.100
Training, inference, cooling, backup: all of it needs electricity.

00:00:36.100 --> 00:00:41.300
IEA puts data centers at about 415 TWh in 2024.

00:00:41.300 --> 00:00:46.300
Its base case points to roughly 945 TWh by 2030.

00:00:46.300 --> 00:00:51.700
Data centers can rise in months. Substations and firm power do not.

00:00:51.700 --> 00:00:56.700
Bitcoin's useful grid case is flexible demand, not magic.

00:00:56.700 --> 00:01:02.700
The future may look like software; underneath it is turbines, transformers, copper, and cooling.
